Package org.daiitech.naftah.parser

Class DefaultNaftahParserVisitor

java.lang.Object
org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
org.daiitech.naftah.parser.NaftahParserBaseVisitor<Object>
org.daiitech.naftah.parser.DefaultNaftahParserVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeVisitor<Object>, NaftahParserVisitor<Object>
public class DefaultNaftahParserVisitor extends NaftahParserBaseVisitor<Object>
The default implementation of the Naftah language visitor.

This class visits and evaluates parse tree nodes generated by the Naftah parser. It provides the interpretation logic for various language constructs such as expressions, statements, operations, and control flows.

Author:
Chakib Daii

      static final Logger LOGGER

    • PARSER_VOCABULARY

      public static org.antlr.v4.runtime.Vocabulary PARSER_VOCABULARY
      The vocabulary used by the parser, typically containing mappings from token names to their symbolic and literal representations. This is often generated by ANTLR and used for error reporting, syntax highlighting, and introspection.

      This field is usually initialized by the parser class generated by ANTLR and provides access to the full vocabulary of the language grammar, including terminals and their associated names.

    • parser

      private final NaftahParser parser
      The ANTLR parser instance that produces the parse tree.

      Current depth in the parse tree traversal.
